               <p>GEORGE SORRELL. I am in the employ of George Dehane, a <rs id="t18301209-136-viclabel777" type="occupation">grocer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-136-victim1223 t18301209-136-viclabel777"></join>, in <placeName id="t18301209-136-crimeloc778">Kingsland-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-136-crimeloc778" type="placeName" value="Kingsland-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-136-crimeloc778" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-136-off775 t18301209-136-crimeloc778"></join>. On the 24th of November, about half-past five o'clock in the afternoon, this soap laid by the side of the door; I missed it, went out, and saw the prisoner with two more twenty or thirty yards from the house - the prisoner was in a stooping position, with a cake of soap in his hand; I took him with it - the other boys were near the rest of it; they got away - I lost eight cakes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-136-person1224">
                  GEORGE 
                  SMITH
